record FpML5.confirmation.FxCounterCurrencyAmount {
  # The non-negative initial rate or amount, as the case may be. An initial rate of 5% would be represented as 0.05.
  initialValue : decimal

  # The schedule of step date and non-negative value pairs. On each step date the associated step value becomes effective. A list of steps may be ordered in the document by ascending step date. An FpML document containing an unordered list of steps is still regarded as a conformant document.
  step : FpML5.confirmation.NonNegativeStep?

  # The currency in which an amount is denominated.
  currency : string

  # In case of multiple counter currency notionals, a strike reference to the appropriate strike may be provided.
  strikeReference : FpML5.confirmation.FxStrikeReference?

  id : string?

}

initialValue.Doc: The non-negative initial rate or amount, as the case may be. An initial rate of 5% would be represented as 0.05.
initialValue.Name: initialValue

step.Name: step

currency.Doc: The currency in which an amount is denominated.
currency.Name: currency

strikeReference.Doc: In case of multiple counter currency notionals, a strike reference to the appropriate strike may be provided.
strikeReference.Name: strikeReference
